        <hr/>
        <h3>Employment</h3>
        <h4>Teaching Assistant</h4>
        <p>University of Ontario Institute of Technology, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />Sep. 2007 to Present
        <br />I work as a Teaching Assistant for both the Environmental Effects
        of Radiation and Radiation Protection courses, through the Faculty of
        Energy Systems and Nuclear Science under Dr. Ed Waller. I am responsible
        for running the laboratory component of these courses in addition to
        marking assignments and lab reports. Through this work I have obtained
        a sound understanding of environmental monitoring and radiation
        protection techniques, including operational skills of LSC's, Air
        Monitors, Gamma Spectroscopy, Alpha/Beta Probes, various health
        physics codes such as VARSKIN and IMBA, and TLD readers.
        </p>
        
        <h4>Research Assistant</h4>
        <p>University of Ontario Institute of Technology, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />May 2007 to Mar. 2010
        <br />I worked with Dr. Anthony Waker and was responsible for
        the background research, as well as experimental design and setup for
        developing a personal tritium monitor using a miniature photomultiplier
        tube. Through various modeling tasks I developed a strong
        understanding of the Monte Carlo Simulation Toolkit GEANT4, which is an
        Object Oriented Toolkit built in C++ that utilizes nuclear libraries for
        customizing a variety of simulation scenarios. 
        </p>
        
        <h4>SecondLife Content Creator</h4>
        <p>University of Ontario Institute of Technology, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />Nov 2006 to Aug. 2007
        <br />I was hired as a contractor for UOIT to begin development on a
        virtual campus in Second Life. Once the initial building was completed
        the focus of the project shifted to creating an interactive learning
        centre for hosting virtual classes. I was required to design and script
        a wide range of applications using Linden Scripting Language (LSL) such
        as a lecture theatre, user interaction HUD, teleportation hubs, and
        streaming video displays.
        </p>
        
        <h4>Executive Officer, Educator</h4>
        <p>Tau Kappa Epsilon, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />Dec. 2005 to Apr. 2009
        <br />I have been able to supervise and work well with others in regards
        to meeting deadlines and serving as a role model. My duties included
        developing and implementing a four year education program for current
        and future fraternity members as well as delegating various tasks and
        responsibilities. I have obtained a sound understanding of student
        consultation and leadership through running the 35 man Chapter with a
        team of 7 other executive officers.
        </p>
        
        <h4>Research Assistant</h4>
        <p>University of Ontario Institute of Technology, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />May 2006 to Sep. 2006
        <br />I worked for Dr. Ed Waller in conjunction with the Department of
        National Defence doing anti-terrorism research in regard to radiological
        dispersal devices. I created several extensive reports including a
        safety procedure for use with a Cascade Impactor. I was responsible for
        a number of projects and received extensive first hand knowledge in
        regards to the research and development industry through hands on
        applications.
        </p>
        
        <h4>Conversion Caller</h4>
        <p>University of Ontario Institute of Technology, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />Jan. 2005 to Apr. 2006
        <br />Played an integral role as part of an over all recruitment team
        that saw enrolment rise by 33% and a rise in applications by 13.5 % in
        2006. I was responsible for calling many perspective students in order
        to answer their questions and concerns in regards to the University and
        student life in and around Durham Region. Being able to effectively
        communicate with thousands of students since 2005 has helped to further
        enhance my communication skills.
        </p>
        
        <h4>UOIT Student Ambassador</h4>
        <p>University of Ontario Institute of Technology, Oshawa, Ontario
        <br />Dec. 2004 to Apr. 2007
        <br />I attended a variety of on-campus events in order to help promote
